snippet.title: AgTech Innovation Summit 2018- Welcome and Morning Keynote
snippet.description:
Speakers:
-Lucas Frye, Amber Agriculture

Lucas Frye is the co-founder of Amber Agriculture, an agtech company focused on introducing precision throughout postharvest processes beginning with grain management. He has two degrees from the University of Illinois, including a bachelor’s degree in Ag Economics and an MBA.

-Germán Bollero, University of Illinois College of ACES

An award-winning teacher and researcher, Germán Bollero previously served as head of the Department of Crop Sciences before accepting his new role as the Associate Dean for Research in the College of Agriculture, Consumer and Environmental Sciences and Director of the Illinois Agricultural Experiment Station. Bollero received his Ph.D. from the University of Illinois in Agronomy.
